1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:02,000
 Have a seat, have a seat.

2
00:00:02,000 --> 00:00:03,500
 It's so wonderful to have you with us.

3
00:00:03,500 --> 00:00:08,000
 We're in the final week of our four-week series on personal transformation.

4
00:00:08,000 --> 00:00:11,000
 Has this series been helping any of you?

5
00:00:11,000 --> 00:00:15,000
 Yeah, like nine of you, great.

6
00:00:15,000 --> 00:00:20,500
 No, I know that actually many of us have been really touched by what we've been doing in this series,

7
00:00:20,500 --> 00:00:24,000
 looking at this pivotal moment in Israel's history,

8
00:00:24,000 --> 00:00:27,000
 a real moment of uncharted time for them,

9
00:00:27,000 --> 00:00:31,000
 where they are miraculously released out of their exile in Babylon

10
00:00:31,000 --> 00:00:34,500
 by the Persian authority and by the king of Persia, Cyrus.

11
00:00:34,500 --> 00:00:39,500
 And they're released back to Jerusalem, a city that they had left some 70 years before.

12
00:00:39,500 --> 00:00:43,000
 And they find themselves standing in the rubble and the ruins of that city,

13
00:00:43,000 --> 00:00:46,000
 of walls which 70 years beforehand had been pulled down,

14
00:00:46,000 --> 00:00:49,000
 a temple that had been destroyed.

15
00:00:49,000 --> 00:00:55,000
 And now they're standing in that rubble and they're asking themselves a big question.

16
00:00:55,000 --> 00:01:00,000
 Can what is rubble today become a glorious temple tomorrow?

17
00:01:00,000 --> 00:01:07,000
 And as they begin to see the first builders come and begin to lay the stones of both the wall that had been broken

18
00:01:07,000 --> 00:01:10,000
 and the temple that had been pulled down,

19
00:01:10,000 --> 00:01:16,000
 both excitement and challenge rise up in the hearts of the people of God,

20
00:01:16,000 --> 00:01:24,000
 believing that God and God alone can take what some think right now looks like destruction

21
00:01:24,000 --> 00:01:28,000
 and turn it into His glory.

22
00:01:28,000 --> 00:01:34,000
 And we've been saying in this series that we're using this moment that we've been looking at from Ezra 3,

23
00:01:34,000 --> 00:01:36,000
 of the rebuilding of the temple.

24
00:01:36,000 --> 00:01:40,000
 We're using this as a metaphor really of what the Lord wants to do in our hearts.

25
00:01:40,000 --> 00:01:43,000
 The reality that for every single one of us, right,

26
00:01:43,000 --> 00:01:47,000
 we know what it is to have things that lie in ruin within us.

27
00:01:47,000 --> 00:01:49,000
 Like those walls in the temple for Israel,

28
00:01:49,000 --> 00:01:56,000
 so for us pain and hurt from our past, trauma that we've struggled to deal with,

29
00:01:56,000 --> 00:02:02,000
 disappointments that we've had, maybe things that have taken place that we regret,

30
00:02:02,000 --> 00:02:08,000
 maybe sin that we're holding or sin in the past that we struggle to let go of,

31
00:02:08,000 --> 00:02:11,000
 maybe suffering that's come upon us, not from any mistake we've made,

32
00:02:11,000 --> 00:02:14,000
 but it's still a suffering that we carry today.

33
00:02:14,000 --> 00:02:19,000
 All of us, we have rubble, we have ruin within us.

34
00:02:19,000 --> 00:02:24,000
 And over this series, we've been speaking about this audacity to believe

35
00:02:24,000 --> 00:02:32,000
 and this hope within us that might say that despite the fact that we can all sense a rubble within us,

36
00:02:32,000 --> 00:02:38,000
 what the enemy meant for evil, the Lord can turn for good.

37
00:02:38,000 --> 00:02:43,000
 And as we finish the series here today, we're not finishing this transformation journey

38
00:02:43,000 --> 00:02:46,000
 that the Lord has for us here at the Vine.

39
00:02:46,000 --> 00:02:49,000
 We're in a very beautiful season right now,

40
00:02:49,000 --> 00:02:53,000
 where the Spirit is moving prophetically and powerfully amongst us.

41
00:02:53,000 --> 00:02:57,000
 And your transformation journey is not a four-week sermon series.

42
00:02:57,000 --> 00:03:06,000
 It is a journey which will lead you beyond here into many twists and turns in the months ahead.

43
00:03:06,000 --> 00:03:10,000
 And so what I want to do in this final message is help to connect you to

44
00:03:10,000 --> 00:03:14,000
 what I think is one of the most significant things that we need to understand

45
00:03:14,000 --> 00:03:18,000
 if we're going to be steadfast in the journey that's ahead.

46
00:03:18,000 --> 00:03:22,000
 And this thing that we're looking at today, it's found in Ezra chapter 3 and 4

47
00:03:22,000 --> 00:03:25,000
 as they're dealing with what's happening with the temple.

48
00:03:25,000 --> 00:03:32,000
 But it's even more beautifully represented for us in the rebuilding of the wall that is found in Nehemiah.

49
00:03:32,000 --> 00:03:35,000
 So although in this series, we've been kind of sat in Ezra,

50
00:03:35,000 --> 00:03:39,000
 I want to shift us now to the book of Nehemiah as we close.

51
00:03:39,000 --> 00:03:42,000
 You might remember in week 1, I spoke about this historic moment

52
00:03:42,000 --> 00:03:49,000
 where the Israelites are in that exile and they're released from exile to go back to Jerusalem in three waves.

53
00:03:49,000 --> 00:03:52,000
 Remember this? So the first wave was Zerubbabel, the leader,

54
00:03:52,000 --> 00:03:55,000
 who led a bunch of people back to rebuild the temple.

55
00:03:55,000 --> 00:04:02,000
 In the second wave, Nehemiah as the leader, brings people back to rebuild the walls that have been broken down.

56
00:04:02,000 --> 00:04:09,000
 And the third wave was Ezra leading the remaining people back to Jerusalem to reestablish the law.

57
00:04:09,000 --> 00:04:11,000
 So we've been looking at Zerubbabel over the last number of weeks.

58
00:04:11,000 --> 00:04:15,000
 I want to finish by looking here today at Nehemiah.

59
00:04:15,000 --> 00:04:23,000
 And as we do this, my prayer for you is that this teaching will be something that will be like a linchpin in your mind,

60
00:04:23,000 --> 00:04:25,000
 like something in your spirit and your heart,

61
00:04:25,000 --> 00:04:30,000
 that you'd be able to take this thing and build on it in the weeks, months, and years ahead.

62
00:04:30,000 --> 00:04:35,000
 I feel like what we're going to be talking about today for some of you will be a shifting point

63
00:04:35,000 --> 00:04:38,000
 in this journey of transformation that you're in.

64
00:04:38,000 --> 00:04:46,000
 Let's start here in Nehemiah chapter 4, and I'm going to start in verse 1.

65
00:04:46,000 --> 00:04:52,000
 Although you can see my page in Ephesians is ripped and it is trying to escape my Bible.

66
00:04:52,000 --> 00:04:54,000
 Sit in the name of Jesus. Okay.

67
00:04:54,000 --> 00:04:56,000
 Nehemiah chapter 4, verse 1.

68
00:04:56,000 --> 00:05:02,000
 "When Sambalat," and I'll explain who that is in a moment, "heard that we were," and this is Nehemiah writing,

69
00:05:02,000 --> 00:05:07,000
 "were rebuilding the wall, he became angry and greatly incensed."

70
00:05:07,000 --> 00:05:10,000
 Let's just stop here for a moment.

71
00:05:10,000 --> 00:05:15,000
 Let me give you some context so that we can kind of really understand this passage and background.

72
00:05:15,000 --> 00:05:19,000
 We know that Israel has been for 70 years in exile in Babylon,

73
00:05:19,000 --> 00:05:24,000
 but we know that the king of Persia, Cyrus, has come and now has released them to go back to Jerusalem.

74
00:05:24,000 --> 00:05:31,000
 And while Jerusalem over those 70 years has laid in ruins, it's not actually been empty.

75
00:05:31,000 --> 00:05:35,000
 Over the seven years that the Israelites, the remnant, have been in exile,

76
00:05:35,000 --> 00:05:42,000
 other nations have come and taken up positions within the city themselves, particularly four nations.

77
00:05:42,000 --> 00:05:44,000
 There was the nation of Samaria.

78
00:05:44,000 --> 00:05:49,000
 So if you remember from week 1 when the Assyrians came down and attacked the 10 tribes that had gone north,

79
00:05:49,000 --> 00:05:54,000
 remember that their policy was to intermarry with the women there, creating a new race

80
00:05:54,000 --> 00:05:59,000
 that was half Jewish, half Gentile, that becomes known as the Samaritans.

81
00:05:59,000 --> 00:06:03,000
 And the Samaritans in the New Testament, we know, are hated by the Jewish people

82
00:06:03,000 --> 00:06:08,000
 because they're a reminder of what happened with this interbreeding between the Gentiles and the Jewish.

83
00:06:08,000 --> 00:06:13,000
 So they were north, and Sambalat is the leader of those people.

84
00:06:13,000 --> 00:06:18,000
 There was also a nation to the right, the Ammonites, and their leader was Tobias.

85
00:06:18,000 --> 00:06:23,000
 There was a nation below who were the Arabians, the people from Arabia in that area.

86
00:06:23,000 --> 00:06:28,000
 And then over on the west side, there was a whole group of people called the people of Ashod.

87
00:06:28,000 --> 00:06:32,000
 Now, both Samaria, the Ammonites, the Arabians, and the people from Ashod

88
00:06:32,000 --> 00:06:38,000
 had moved in and taken up occupation of certain areas of Jerusalem, totally illegally.

89
00:06:38,000 --> 00:06:42,000
 But in their minds, they were thinking, "Well, the Jewish people have been desecrated.

90
00:06:42,000 --> 00:06:47,000
 They're never coming back. We may as well take some of this land for ourselves."

91
00:06:47,000 --> 00:06:53,000
 But now that Persia oversaw the land, and the king had given Nehemiah and Edith

92
00:06:53,000 --> 00:06:57,000
 for him to have the permission from the king to rebuild the walls,

93
00:06:57,000 --> 00:07:05,000
 those people who had been occupying that space begin to realize that their time now is very limited.

94
00:07:05,000 --> 00:07:12,000
 And we see in the Scripture here that Sambalat, as he sees Israel beginning to rebuild the fortifications of their city,

95
00:07:12,000 --> 00:07:16,000
 he's angry and greatly incensed. And this is understandable.

96
00:07:16,000 --> 00:07:21,000
 Because what's going to happen here is that through him and a bunch of his cronies,

97
00:07:21,000 --> 00:07:27,000
 they're going to bring opposition to the wall and the rebuilding process.

98
00:07:27,000 --> 00:07:31,000
 We also see this opposition that comes to the rebuilding of the temple.

99
00:07:31,000 --> 00:07:36,000
 And it's fascinating, because no matter what the Lord might be doing upon us,

100
00:07:36,000 --> 00:07:40,000
 no matter what transformation process that we are in,

101
00:07:40,000 --> 00:07:48,000
 even if it has been God-ordained, God-chosen, the reality is the enemy is not going to like it.

102
00:07:48,000 --> 00:07:52,000
 The reality is that the enemy is going to turn his face against it.

103
00:07:52,000 --> 00:07:56,000
 The reality is that there is going to be opposition.

104
00:07:56,000 --> 00:07:59,000
 And here's how often that opposition takes place.

105
00:07:59,000 --> 00:08:07,000
 Usually it comes from the people who are going to be stripped of their power if we are changed and transformed.

106
00:08:07,000 --> 00:08:14,000
 Opposition so often comes from the very voices of those who are likely to be threatened

107
00:08:14,000 --> 00:08:19,000
 in their own authority or their own power by your transformation.

108
00:08:19,000 --> 00:08:25,000
 And here is Sambalat and his buddies, and they're seeing that if Israel re-fortified their walls,

109
00:08:25,000 --> 00:08:30,000
 their power is going to go. And so he's angry, he's greatly incensed,

110
00:08:30,000 --> 00:08:34,000
 and he brings opposition to this process of rebuilding.

111
00:08:34,000 --> 00:08:41,000
 Now I don't know about you, but this might seem somewhat kind of weird and kind of strange what's happening here.

112
00:08:41,000 --> 00:08:46,000
 Because as Christians we can often think, don't we, that, you know, "Hey, God's called me to this.

113
00:08:46,000 --> 00:08:50,000
 God's asked me to do this. This is actually God's project. It's not mine.

114
00:08:50,000 --> 00:08:53,000
 He's the one who's giving me hope and faith.

115
00:08:53,000 --> 00:08:56,000
 He's the one who's asked me to focus on this transformation process that I'm in.

116
00:08:56,000 --> 00:09:00,000
 If God's in it, well, surely I'm going to be blessed.

117
00:09:00,000 --> 00:09:04,000
 Well, surely if God's in it, everything's going to be fine, right?

118
00:09:04,000 --> 00:09:09,000
 Like if God has called me to it, then surely it's going to be smooth sailing."

119
00:09:09,000 --> 00:09:16,000
 You have to understand that perhaps one of the most damaging and yet attractive false gospels that there is

120
00:09:16,000 --> 00:09:24,000
 is the one that says that because you are in the will of God, everything's going to be easy.

121
00:09:24,000 --> 00:09:27,000
 Come on, church, that is a false gospel.

122
00:09:27,000 --> 00:09:33,000
 In fact, you can go through the pages of Scripture and you can see some of the greatest heroes of the faith

123
00:09:33,000 --> 00:09:36,000
 and they will tell you that their story was something different.

124
00:09:36,000 --> 00:09:39,000
 That, yeah, God had called them. Yes, God had equipped them.

125
00:09:39,000 --> 00:09:43,000
 God had a great plan and a purpose for their lives and they stepped out in faith.

126
00:09:43,000 --> 00:09:45,000
 But man, did they come up against opposition.

127
00:09:45,000 --> 00:09:49,000
 Man, was it challenging. Man, was it difficult. Man, was it hard.

128
00:09:49,000 --> 00:09:53,000
 Man, was there their time where they wanted to give up, where they wanted to go.

129
00:09:53,000 --> 00:09:58,000
 They realized so often through the journey that they were weak, that they didn't have it.

130
00:09:58,000 --> 00:10:02,000
 But every time they would say, "Look, God called me to this.

131
00:10:02,000 --> 00:10:05,000
 He's faithful, but that does not mean it's easy.

132
00:10:05,000 --> 00:10:09,000
 That doesn't mean that this is all going to go smooth sailing.

133
00:10:09,000 --> 00:10:14,000
 It doesn't mean that it's all going to be rainbows and my little ponies."

134
00:10:14,000 --> 00:10:17,000
 Here's the true gospel.

135
00:10:17,000 --> 00:10:24,000
 The true gospel is that we have a God who doesn't miraculously just suddenly remove opposition from us.

136
00:10:24,000 --> 00:10:29,000
 We have a God who's decided to come down and stand in that opposition with us.

137
00:10:29,000 --> 00:10:35,000
 We have a God where the true gospel is a God who's willing to suffer,

138
00:10:35,000 --> 00:10:38,000
 who's willing to feel pain, who's willing to stand in the gap,

139
00:10:38,000 --> 00:10:48,000
 who's willing to walk the hard yards knowing that it is only through death and resurrection that true life can come.

140
00:10:48,000 --> 00:10:52,000
 You know, Jesus himself was tempted by this false gospel.

141
00:10:52,000 --> 00:10:56,000
 Remember that moment where just after his baptism, before he starts his ministry,

142
00:10:56,000 --> 00:11:03,000
 the Holy Spirit leads him into the wilderness to be tested by Satan for 40 days and nights.

143
00:11:03,000 --> 00:11:09,000
 And the second of those temptations is that Satan takes Jesus up to the top of this high mountain

144
00:11:09,000 --> 00:11:14,000
 and he shows him all of the nations of the world in their glory and their splendor.

145
00:11:14,000 --> 00:11:16,000
 And Satan says this to Jesus.

146
00:11:16,000 --> 00:11:19,000
 He says, "Jesus, if you just worship me, I'll give everything to you."

147
00:11:19,000 --> 00:11:23,000
 See, Jesus knew that his calling was to redeem the world.

148
00:11:23,000 --> 00:11:28,000
 And here's Satan saying, "You can take the world without the cross.

149
00:11:28,000 --> 00:11:34,000
 You can take the My Little Pony route if you just worship me."

150
00:11:34,000 --> 00:11:39,000
 And we know in the story that Jesus resists that temptation, quotes Scripture at Satan,

151
00:11:39,000 --> 00:11:44,000
 and makes the choice not just then but every step of the way to say,

152
00:11:44,000 --> 00:11:49,000
 "Even though it's going to be super hard, super difficult, it's going to be painful,

153
00:11:49,000 --> 00:11:53,000
 there's going to be suffering involved, I know that the way to true redemption

154
00:11:53,000 --> 00:11:57,000
 is not to worship somebody who's going to suddenly give it all to me.

155
00:11:57,000 --> 00:12:00,000
 It's to actually pay the price for the world's sin on my shoulders

156
00:12:00,000 --> 00:12:05,000
 through the pain of the cross and the wonder of the resurrection."

157
00:12:05,000 --> 00:12:12,000
 And the gospel sits on this profound idea that our God was willing to suffer.

158
00:12:12,000 --> 00:12:18,000
 And in the beauty of the resurrection, we have a God who has, as we've just seen from that song

159
00:12:18,000 --> 00:12:23,000
 and as we've just read from the book of Ephesians, that now he is seated at the right hand of the Father

160
00:12:23,000 --> 00:12:27,000
 and there's no other title, no other name, no other power that is higher than him.

161
00:12:27,000 --> 00:12:35,000
 Everything is under his feet and in the wonder of that power, he has poured out his love to the church.

162
00:12:35,000 --> 00:12:40,000
 See, the wonder of the gospel that we stand for is that we have a God

163
00:12:40,000 --> 00:12:46,000
 who meets us in our place of death and resurrection.

164
00:12:46,000 --> 00:12:50,000
 This is why Jesus himself said, "If you want to follow me,

165
00:12:50,000 --> 00:12:55,000
 you're going to need to have to deny yourself and pick up your cross.

166
00:12:55,000 --> 00:12:57,000
 Then you can follow me."

167
00:12:57,000 --> 00:13:02,000
 That's why in the New Testament, the writers like Paul and Peter and others

168
00:13:02,000 --> 00:13:06,000
 speak so often about our own journey of death and resurrection.

169
00:13:06,000 --> 00:13:12,000
 Paul saying these wonderful words in Corinthians saying, "I'm willing to take the dying side

170
00:13:12,000 --> 00:13:16,000
 if that means you can have the rising side."

171
00:13:16,000 --> 00:13:21,000
 So our gospel is not, "If you're in the will of God, everything's going to be great."

172
00:13:21,000 --> 00:13:30,000
 Our gospel is, "Sometimes the will of God means things are going to feel like death and resurrection."

173
00:13:30,000 --> 00:13:35,000
 So the sober reality is if you're in a season of personal transformation in your life, hear this,

174
00:13:35,000 --> 00:13:38,000
 you are going to be opposed.

175
00:13:38,000 --> 00:13:41,000
 It's going to be hard. It's going to be tough.

176
00:13:41,000 --> 00:13:43,000
 There's going to be some pain involved.

177
00:13:43,000 --> 00:13:46,000
 And that opposition is going to come from people around you

178
00:13:46,000 --> 00:13:51,000
 who feel like their power is being stripped because you are getting better.

179
00:13:51,000 --> 00:13:57,000
 That opposition is going to come from unjust systemic issues in society around us.

180
00:13:57,000 --> 00:14:02,000
 That opposition is going to come directly from satanic influence in our lives.

181
00:14:02,000 --> 00:14:07,000
 And also hear this, that opposition is going to come from yourself.

182
00:14:07,000 --> 00:14:09,000
 The way you think about yourself.

183
00:14:09,000 --> 00:14:12,000
 The way you reflect on yourself.

184
00:14:12,000 --> 00:14:14,000
 What you believe about yourself.

185
00:14:14,000 --> 00:14:16,000
 How you see your identity.

186
00:14:16,000 --> 00:14:23,000
 Sometimes we're our worst enemy and sometimes the greatest opposition to the movement of the Lord in our lives

187
00:14:23,000 --> 00:14:24,000
 is not everything else I just talked about.

188
00:14:24,000 --> 00:14:33,000
 It's merely the fact that we are preaching a false gospel to ourselves.

189
00:14:33,000 --> 00:14:40,000
 The beautiful thing we have is that in Nehemiah 4, 5, and 6, just these three chapters,

190
00:14:40,000 --> 00:14:43,000
 we see the story of the rebuilding of the walls of Jerusalem.

191
00:14:43,000 --> 00:14:49,000
 And in this we see specific moments of opposition to that rebuilding.

192
00:14:49,000 --> 00:14:54,000
 And as we study these chapters, what you can learn are some great tips, if you will.

193
00:14:54,000 --> 00:15:00,000
 Some great understanding of what opposition is going to look like in your journey.

194
00:15:00,000 --> 00:15:04,000
 And so for Israel and theirs, I think also for us,

195
00:15:04,000 --> 00:15:08,000
 what we're just about to look at in a moment is how opposition comes for Israel

196
00:15:08,000 --> 00:15:10,000
 in the rebuilding of the wall in three times.

197
00:15:10,000 --> 00:15:14,000
 Right at the start of the process of the building, right in the middle of the process,

198
00:15:14,000 --> 00:15:17,000
 and just before completion at the end.

199
00:15:17,000 --> 00:15:22,000
 And in your own journey of personal transformation, the same is going to happen to you.

200
00:15:22,000 --> 00:15:26,000
 These attacks could happen at any time, but you are going to have profound opposition when you start.

201
00:15:26,000 --> 00:15:29,000
 You're going to have some profound opposition in the middle.

202
00:15:29,000 --> 00:15:33,000
 And you're going to be really oppressed right towards the end.

203
00:15:33,000 --> 00:15:39,000
 And these oppositions are designed to make sure that you never complete

204
00:15:39,000 --> 00:15:43,000
 the transformation that the Lord has on His heart for you.

205
00:15:43,000 --> 00:15:48,000
 And so I'm really excited because we're actually going to expose these enemy strategies here this morning.

206
00:15:48,000 --> 00:15:52,000
 And as we expose these and look at these three oppositions that come,

207
00:15:52,000 --> 00:15:57,000
 my prayer is that this will equip you to be stronger in the journey that you're in.

208
00:15:57,000 --> 00:16:03,000
 Remember, this is not going to equip you to never be opposed, to never feel these oppositions.

209
00:16:03,000 --> 00:16:10,000
 Instead, I'm hoping it will give in your mind and in your spirit an understanding of the way that the enemy works,

210
00:16:10,000 --> 00:16:16,000
 but also a way in which the Lord renews and redeems even within it.

211
00:16:16,000 --> 00:16:23,000
 So Father, I pray that as we open Your Word here this morning, this would be life for every single one of us.

212
00:16:23,000 --> 00:16:29,000
 Lord, we all recognize some of the opposition that is against us, external to us,

213
00:16:29,000 --> 00:16:32,000
 and also internal in our own narrative.

214
00:16:32,000 --> 00:16:39,000
 Lord, we want to pray that as we move forward as a church in the months ahead to this journey of transformation,

215
00:16:39,000 --> 00:16:46,000
 that what we see in Your Word today would be the very rear guard that we need for all the things that are ahead.

216
00:16:46,000 --> 00:16:48,000
 We pray this in Jesus' name.

217
00:16:48,000 --> 00:16:50,000
 So let's go back to Nehemiah 4, verse 1.

218
00:16:50,000 --> 00:16:56,000
 So the very first opposition that will always come in a season of personal transformation,

219
00:16:56,000 --> 00:17:02,000
 often at the start of that season, is the opposition of ridicule.

220
00:17:02,000 --> 00:17:05,000
 Let me read this to you from Nehemiah 4, first three verses.

221
00:17:05,000 --> 00:17:11,000
 "When Sambalat heard that they were rebuilding the wall, he became angry and was greatly incensed.

222
00:17:11,000 --> 00:17:19,000
 He ridiculed the Jews, and in the presence of his associates and the army of Samaria, he said, 'What are these feeble Jews doing?

223
00:17:19,000 --> 00:17:25,000
 Will they restore their wall? Will they offer their sacrifices? Will they finish in a day?

224
00:17:25,000 --> 00:17:31,000
 Can they bring the stones back to life from the heaps of rubble that they are, burned as they are?'

225
00:17:31,000 --> 00:17:36,000
 Tobiah the Ammonite, who was at his side, said this, 'Ah, what they are building!

226
00:17:36,000 --> 00:17:43,000
 If even a fox climbed up on it, he would break down their walls of stone. Ha, ha, ha, ha, ha, ha, ha!'"

227
00:17:43,000 --> 00:17:45,000
 Can you hear it?

228
00:17:45,000 --> 00:17:49,000
 These two guys are like, you know, in the Muppets, the grumpy old men on the balcony?

229
00:17:49,000 --> 00:17:52,000
 That's like what these two guys are.

230
00:17:52,000 --> 00:17:57,000
 And it's always like, I love Tobiah, it's like Sambalat is saying all these things against Israel,

231
00:17:57,000 --> 00:18:02,000
 and Tobiah is like the small guy standing next to him, and at the end he's like, throws in his two pieces,

232
00:18:02,000 --> 00:18:09,000
 and it's about some fox climbing on them, and you can almost feel Sambalat going, "Shut up!"

233
00:18:09,000 --> 00:18:15,000
 Ridicule is the central opposition that will come to you at the beginning of a building process,

234
00:18:15,000 --> 00:18:17,000
 the beginning of a rebuilding of something in your life.

235
00:18:17,000 --> 00:18:21,000
 At this point, they have begun to rebuild the walls.

236
00:18:21,000 --> 00:18:27,000
 The first stones are being put into place, and Sambalat begins to speak this ridicule over Israel,

237
00:18:27,000 --> 00:18:32,000
 because the plan is to try to disrupt them right at the start.

238
00:18:32,000 --> 00:18:35,000
 And Sambalat begins by saying a couple of questions.

239
00:18:35,000 --> 00:18:36,000
 Let me break these down quickly.

240
00:18:36,000 --> 00:18:39,000
 He says, first of all, what are these feeble Jews doing?

241
00:18:39,000 --> 00:18:40,000
 I love this.

242
00:18:40,000 --> 00:18:47,000
 Sambalat starts by saying, "You're feeble! Do you really think that you can do this project?"

243
00:18:47,000 --> 00:18:54,000
 The word in the Hebrew that Nehemiah uses for feeble here is a word that normally is associated with plants,

244
00:18:54,000 --> 00:18:58,000
 and the idea of a plant withering, like a plant dying and withering.

245
00:18:58,000 --> 00:19:06,000
 And he starts by saying, "Will these withering Jewish people be able to have any strength whatsoever?"

246
00:19:06,000 --> 00:19:07,000
 Now, this is really important.

247
00:19:07,000 --> 00:19:10,000
 I want you to see something here.

248
00:19:10,000 --> 00:19:16,000
 The reason why ridicule is so powerful, particularly at the beginning of a transformation process,

249
00:19:16,000 --> 00:19:21,000
 is because ridicule often comes with an element of truth.

250
00:19:21,000 --> 00:19:24,000
 The most powerful ridicule that will be impactful in your life

251
00:19:24,000 --> 00:19:29,000
 are those ridicules that connect with something that might be actually true in you.

252
00:19:29,000 --> 00:19:34,000
 Because at this point in time, actually, Israel is withered.

253
00:19:34,000 --> 00:19:39,000
 They are a very small reflection of the strength of the nation that they were 70 years ago.

254
00:19:39,000 --> 00:19:44,000
 Whilst they don't use the word "withered" about themselves, the word that is used is "remnant."

255
00:19:44,000 --> 00:19:46,000
 They're a remnant of what they used to be.

256
00:19:46,000 --> 00:19:48,000
 They don't have that powerful city they used to have.

257
00:19:48,000 --> 00:19:50,000
 They don't have a powerful army anymore.

258
00:19:50,000 --> 00:19:56,000
 There's just a few feeble groups of Jewish people that are believing in a God

259
00:19:56,000 --> 00:19:59,000
 who can do everything greater than they would ever do.

260
00:19:59,000 --> 00:20:01,000
 But ridicule hurts.

261
00:20:01,000 --> 00:20:07,000
 Ridicule has power because there's an element of truth within it.

262
00:20:07,000 --> 00:20:11,000
 Oh, you want to be an entrepreneur?

263
00:20:11,000 --> 00:20:13,000
 You want to be an entrepreneur?

264
00:20:13,000 --> 00:20:18,000
 You can't even hold down a job, let alone run your own business.

265
00:20:18,000 --> 00:20:23,000
 Oh, you want to get married?

266
00:20:23,000 --> 00:20:25,000
 Sorry, sorry.

267
00:20:25,000 --> 00:20:27,000
 You want to get married?

268
00:20:27,000 --> 00:20:32,000
 Have you looked in the mirror lately?

269
00:20:32,000 --> 00:20:35,000
 I wasn't pointing at anyone, by the way.

270
00:20:35,000 --> 00:20:38,000
 There's like a dead space over here.

271
00:20:38,000 --> 00:20:40,000
 I'm pointing at the dead space.

272
00:20:40,000 --> 00:20:41,000
 But we know, right?

273
00:20:41,000 --> 00:20:46,000
 Ridicule actually really hurts because it picks up on a half-truth inside of us.

274
00:20:46,000 --> 00:20:48,000
 Yeah, I actually have failed in my business before.

275
00:20:48,000 --> 00:20:50,000
 Why would I think that this time I'm going to do better?

276
00:20:50,000 --> 00:20:53,000
 Yeah, I guess I'm not in the physical shape that I thought I would always be in.

277
00:20:53,000 --> 00:20:55,000
 And I guess I'm not going to be attractive to anyone.

278
00:20:55,000 --> 00:20:56,000
 Or whatever it is.

279
00:20:56,000 --> 00:20:59,000
 But we wrestle, don't we, with these half-truths.

280
00:20:59,000 --> 00:21:02,000
 Now, I want you to see what the ridicule connected to truth is trying to do.

281
00:21:02,000 --> 00:21:06,000
 It's trying to highlight something that might be true in you,

282
00:21:06,000 --> 00:21:09,000
 but that isn't important to God.

283
00:21:09,000 --> 00:21:11,000
 So it might be true in you.

284
00:21:11,000 --> 00:21:12,000
 Yeah, I am feeling a bit weak.

285
00:21:12,000 --> 00:21:13,000
 Yeah, I guess I've always failed.

286
00:21:13,000 --> 00:21:15,000
 Yes, I feel bad about myself.

287
00:21:15,000 --> 00:21:17,000
 And God is saying, "That's actually not the important thing here."

288
00:21:17,000 --> 00:21:19,000
 But what ridicule does is it picks up on that.

289
00:21:19,000 --> 00:21:26,000
 And what it causes us to do is stop thinking about God and start thinking about ourselves.

290
00:21:26,000 --> 00:21:31,000
 It means that we begin to put our place, ourself, in the center place.

291
00:21:31,000 --> 00:21:33,000
 Right at the beginning of the project.

292
00:21:33,000 --> 00:21:37,000
 When we should be going, "Hey, God's in this. God's called me.

293
00:21:37,000 --> 00:21:39,000
 I don't think I have all the strength inside of me.

294
00:21:39,000 --> 00:21:43,000
 But you know what? I'm going to walk in faith, believing that He can equip me.

295
00:21:43,000 --> 00:21:44,000
 He can resource me.

296
00:21:44,000 --> 00:21:47,000
 He can do things that I never thought I could ever do.

297
00:21:47,000 --> 00:21:50,000
 I'm going to put my trust in a God who is able to do immeasurably more

298
00:21:50,000 --> 00:21:55,000
 than ever I could ask or imagine according to the power that is at work in the church."

299
00:21:55,000 --> 00:21:56,000
 Or whatever it might be.

300
00:21:56,000 --> 00:21:57,000
 But we begin to stand up.

301
00:21:57,000 --> 00:22:03,000
 Rather than do that, we begin to think, "Yeah, I guess the ridicule's right.

302
00:22:03,000 --> 00:22:05,000
 I guess I am feeble.

303
00:22:05,000 --> 00:22:07,000
 I guess I don't have it."

304
00:22:07,000 --> 00:22:11,000
 And this feeble attack attacks physical identity.

305
00:22:11,000 --> 00:22:14,000
 How we see ourselves.

306
00:22:14,000 --> 00:22:16,000
 But notice his second question.

307
00:22:16,000 --> 00:22:17,000
 He then goes on.

308
00:22:17,000 --> 00:22:20,000
 He says, "Will they restore their wall?"

309
00:22:20,000 --> 00:22:22,000
 The first one is attack on physical identity.

310
00:22:22,000 --> 00:22:27,000
 The second one, still ridicule, is the attack on their actual mental strength.

311
00:22:27,000 --> 00:22:30,000
 Do you really think you can do it?

312
00:22:30,000 --> 00:22:31,000
 Do you think you have the ability?

313
00:22:31,000 --> 00:22:33,000
 Do you think you can restore the wall?

314
00:22:33,000 --> 00:22:35,000
 Will they restore the project?

315
00:22:35,000 --> 00:22:36,000
 Hey, you're right at the start.

316
00:22:36,000 --> 00:22:38,000
 There's a long way to go.

317
00:22:38,000 --> 00:22:41,000
 Have you seen how much rubble is around right now?

318
00:22:41,000 --> 00:22:43,000
 Do you really think?

319
00:22:43,000 --> 00:22:47,000
 Because if you think that, you've got to go check out some mental health class or something.

320
00:22:47,000 --> 00:22:53,000
 Because ridicule picks up on attacking not just our physical identity and how we see ourselves,

321
00:22:53,000 --> 00:22:59,000
 but the way in which we think, the way in which our mind is, our mental strength.

322
00:22:59,000 --> 00:23:01,000
 Will they restore their wall?

323
00:23:01,000 --> 00:23:04,000
 It's almost like Sam Black's taking bets in front of them.

324
00:23:04,000 --> 00:23:07,000
 "You're never going to do this."

325
00:23:07,000 --> 00:23:12,000
 And the third thing he says, which I think is really interesting, he says, "Will they offer sacrifices?"

326
00:23:12,000 --> 00:23:15,000
 So he's attacked through ridicule their physical identity.

327
00:23:15,000 --> 00:23:19,000
 He's then attacked their mental identity, the way they think.

328
00:23:19,000 --> 00:23:22,000
 He's now attacking their spiritual identity.

329
00:23:22,000 --> 00:23:24,000
 Will you offer sacrifices?

330
00:23:24,000 --> 00:23:27,000
 You can almost hear the taunt that Sam Black is saying here.

331
00:23:27,000 --> 00:23:28,000
 Remember, think about the history.

332
00:23:28,000 --> 00:23:35,000
 You can almost hear Sam Black saying, "Your forefathers, they offered sacrifices right here in this city.

333
00:23:35,000 --> 00:23:38,000
 Oh, you used to have a beautiful temple where you offered sacrifices all the time."

334
00:23:38,000 --> 00:23:41,000
 Look how that turned out for them.

335
00:23:41,000 --> 00:23:46,000
 Like, have you seen that your forefathers put their faith in this God who turned His back on you?

336
00:23:46,000 --> 00:23:51,000
 You went into exile, and now you've returned, and this place is a rubble amongst you.

337
00:23:51,000 --> 00:23:55,000
 You're going to trust the same God that your forefathers trusted?

338
00:23:55,000 --> 00:23:58,000
 Okay, go ahead. Let's see how that's going to turn out.

339
00:23:58,000 --> 00:24:01,000
 Are you really going to offer sacrifices to that one?

340
00:24:01,000 --> 00:24:04,000
 Let me tell you about another God that you can offer sacrifices to.

341
00:24:04,000 --> 00:24:07,000
 One who can really help you.

342
00:24:07,000 --> 00:24:10,000
 For all of us, when ridicule hits us right at the start of the project,

343
00:24:10,000 --> 00:24:13,000
 right at the start of a season of transformation,

344
00:24:13,000 --> 00:24:18,000
 we're very tempted to begin to second-guess what God has been saying to us,

345
00:24:18,000 --> 00:24:20,000
 second-guess our trust in Him,

346
00:24:20,000 --> 00:24:24,000
 second-guess the things that He's spoken into us by His Word or prayer,

347
00:24:24,000 --> 00:24:28,000
 or somebody said something to us, and it's given us that impetus to begin.

348
00:24:28,000 --> 00:24:34,000
 But very quickly, as ridicule comes, it begins to attack the very basic foundation of our faith.

349
00:24:34,000 --> 00:24:39,000
 "Yeah, I don't know. Did God really say that? Is God really going to come through?"

350
00:24:39,000 --> 00:24:42,000
 "Yeah, I've seen Him come through for others, but yeah, let me stop and think about it.

351
00:24:42,000 --> 00:24:46,000
 Actually, so many of my prayers are unanswered.

352
00:24:46,000 --> 00:24:50,000
 So many. Yeah, everybody else needs to have a testimony about how great God is,

353
00:24:50,000 --> 00:24:56,000
 but if I think about my life, I'm not sure if it's really true for me."

354
00:24:56,000 --> 00:25:01,000
 So here's Sambalat, and he's using ridicule to attack the three essential things,

355
00:25:01,000 --> 00:25:06,000
 physical identity, mental strength, spiritual life, spiritual identity.

356
00:25:06,000 --> 00:25:09,000
 And when we, as people, are under this opposition,

357
00:25:09,000 --> 00:25:13,000
 we begin to believe what ridicule is saying to us,

358
00:25:13,000 --> 00:25:16,000
 here's the two things that are always going to happen.

359
00:25:16,000 --> 00:25:20,000
 He mentions this. He says, "Will they finish in a day?"

360
00:25:20,000 --> 00:25:24,000
 When we allow, right at the start, and this is why ridicule comes at the beginning of a process,

361
00:25:24,000 --> 00:25:27,000
 when we allow the ridicule to come right at the start, here's what we begin to think.

362
00:25:27,000 --> 00:25:31,000
 Because of my physical identity, because of that thinking, because of the spiritual stuff,

363
00:25:31,000 --> 00:25:36,000
 because everything now is in doubt, I'm thinking there's no way this could ever happen.

364
00:25:36,000 --> 00:25:40,000
 There's no way this will happen. I can't finish this.

365
00:25:40,000 --> 00:25:46,000
 It's not going to take place, and we're tempted to put down the tools straight away.

366
00:25:46,000 --> 00:25:49,000
 Look at the second, or the final one. He says this.

367
00:25:49,000 --> 00:25:53,000
 "Can they bring the stones back to life from the heaps of rubble, burned as they are?

368
00:25:53,000 --> 00:25:56,000
 Not only do we second guess whether we can do it,

369
00:25:56,000 --> 00:26:00,000
 we then second guess the resources God has given us to do it."

370
00:26:00,000 --> 00:26:03,000
 Well, yeah, what about these stones? Yeah, they are burned out.

371
00:26:03,000 --> 00:26:05,000
 Yeah, I don't know. I mean, I don't even know if we can do this.

372
00:26:05,000 --> 00:26:09,000
 I don't even know the resources. This is what ridicule will do to you.

373
00:26:09,000 --> 00:26:14,000
 It'll cause you to doubt everything God has already said to you.

374
00:26:14,000 --> 00:26:17,000
 And it's right there at the start to stop that process.

375
00:26:17,000 --> 00:26:21,000
 So let me pull all the threads together of this first one, and let me read it to you like this.

376
00:26:21,000 --> 00:26:23,000
 I want to just make this clear.

377
00:26:23,000 --> 00:26:28,000
 "Ridicule is designed to make us doubt that we have the physical, mental, or spiritual ability

378
00:26:28,000 --> 00:26:32,000
 to achieve the transformation God longs for us.

379
00:26:32,000 --> 00:26:35,000
 If we don't fight this ridicule, we will agree with the enemy

380
00:26:35,000 --> 00:26:38,000
 that our transformation is too large to be accomplished,

381
00:26:38,000 --> 00:26:43,000
 and we don't have the right resources to achieve it.

382
00:26:43,000 --> 00:26:50,000
 And because of that, we choose to stay in ruins."

383
00:26:50,000 --> 00:26:55,000
 The second opposition that will come to you in any season of personal transformation,

384
00:26:55,000 --> 00:26:59,000
 which often happens in the middle of that transformation process,

385
00:26:59,000 --> 00:27:03,000
 is the opposition of feeling overwhelmed.

386
00:27:03,000 --> 00:27:07,000
 I watched a movie last night with my daughter, and there was a line in the movie.

387
00:27:07,000 --> 00:27:17,000
 It was like, "You can be overwhelmed, and you can be underwhelmed, but can you just be whelmed?"

388
00:27:17,000 --> 00:27:20,000
 You know the movie, you get an extra star.

389
00:27:20,000 --> 00:27:24,000
 But this idea, when we're in the middle of a transformation process,

390
00:27:24,000 --> 00:27:27,000
 this is where things can get really challenging for us.

391
00:27:27,000 --> 00:27:30,000
 Because we've already done some work, we've already strengthened something,

392
00:27:30,000 --> 00:27:32,000
 but now we're in the middle of it, we're feeling a little bit tired,

393
00:27:32,000 --> 00:27:35,000
 and we're wondering, "Can we keep going?"

394
00:27:35,000 --> 00:27:40,000
 Let me show you this from Nehemiah 4, just verse 6 onwards.

395
00:27:40,000 --> 00:27:44,000
 Nehemiah says, "So we rebuilt the wall till all of it reached about half of its height,

396
00:27:44,000 --> 00:27:46,000
 for the people worked with all of their hearts."

397
00:27:46,000 --> 00:27:50,000
 So they're halfway done. It's reached half of its height.

398
00:27:50,000 --> 00:27:55,000
 "But when Sambalat," there he is again, "Tobiah and the Arabs and the Ammonites and the men of Ashod

399
00:27:55,000 --> 00:27:58,000
 heard that the repairs of Jerusalem's wall had gone ahead

400
00:27:58,000 --> 00:28:03,000
 and that there were gaps being closed, they were very angry.

401
00:28:03,000 --> 00:28:08,000
 They all plotted together to come and fight against Jerusalem, to stir up trouble against it.

402
00:28:08,000 --> 00:28:12,000
 But we prayed to our God and posted a guard day and night to meet this threat.

403
00:28:12,000 --> 00:28:17,000
 Meanwhile, the people in Judas said, 'The strength of the laborers is giving out,

404
00:28:17,000 --> 00:28:21,000
 and there is so much rubble that we cannot rebuild the wall.'

405
00:28:21,000 --> 00:28:26,000
 Also our enemy said, 'Before they know it or see us, we will be right there among them,

406
00:28:26,000 --> 00:28:29,000
 and we will kill them and put an end to the work.'

407
00:28:29,000 --> 00:28:34,000
 Then the Jews who lived near the wall, they came and told us ten times over,

408
00:28:34,000 --> 00:28:38,000
 'Wherever you turn, they will attack us.'"

409
00:28:38,000 --> 00:28:41,000
 All right, I want you to see what's happening here.

410
00:28:41,000 --> 00:28:46,000
 In the middle of the process, the armies and the enemies against Israel and the rebuilding of the wall

411
00:28:46,000 --> 00:28:52,000
 decide for a full frontal attack on Israel, and they decide to surround Israel.

412
00:28:52,000 --> 00:28:57,000
 Samaria from the north, the Ammonites from the east, the Arabians from the south,

413
00:28:57,000 --> 00:28:59,000
 the people of Ashod from the west.

414
00:28:59,000 --> 00:29:03,000
 They're coming in and they're closing in on God's people,

415
00:29:03,000 --> 00:29:06,000
 and they're closing in with the threat of physical attack,

416
00:29:06,000 --> 00:29:10,000
 with the threat of actually trying to stop them physically from rebuilding the wall.

417
00:29:10,000 --> 00:29:16,000
 And we can see what this just threat of being surrounded is doing to God's people.

418
00:29:16,000 --> 00:29:20,000
 Notice they say this, "The strength of the laborers is giving out.

419
00:29:20,000 --> 00:29:24,000
 Wherever you turn, they're going to attack us."

420
00:29:24,000 --> 00:29:28,000
 There's fear being risen up within Israel,

421
00:29:28,000 --> 00:29:33,000
 because they're feeling kind of surrounded by attack on all sides.

422
00:29:33,000 --> 00:29:38,000
 The feeling of being overwhelmed is one of the primary ways

423
00:29:38,000 --> 00:29:45,000
 that the enemy will try to get you to stop your transformation process right in the middle of it.

424
00:29:45,000 --> 00:29:49,000
 I wonder if you've ever had an experience where you feel like everything is all around you,

425
00:29:49,000 --> 00:29:53,000
 hemming you in, and you feel like there's no escape, and you don't know what to do.

426
00:29:53,000 --> 00:29:55,000
 Anyone ever felt that way?

427
00:29:55,000 --> 00:29:59,000
 Just me and you.

428
00:29:59,000 --> 00:30:03,000
 Here you go, brother.

429
00:30:03,000 --> 00:30:06,000
 Everybody else does as well, but they just won't admit it.

430
00:30:06,000 --> 00:30:08,000
 So we all know that feeling, don't we?

431
00:30:08,000 --> 00:30:12,000
 Of being hemmed in all around by everything coming against us at the same time,

432
00:30:12,000 --> 00:30:14,000
 and us feeling so overwhelmed.

433
00:30:14,000 --> 00:30:16,000
 And here's what the feeling will do.

434
00:30:16,000 --> 00:30:20,000
 Like this strength will be sapped from us for the work that we have.

435
00:30:20,000 --> 00:30:23,000
 We'll fear that we'll be attacked all the time.

436
00:30:23,000 --> 00:30:26,000
 And so what we want to do is move away from that project.

437
00:30:26,000 --> 00:30:31,000
 It's a fight or flight type thing, and we choose flight every time.

438
00:30:31,000 --> 00:30:35,000
 We want to turn around, turn away, protect ourselves,

439
00:30:35,000 --> 00:30:41,000
 because the attack is coming from all around us.

440
00:30:41,000 --> 00:30:44,000
 Now this is the reason why this happens in the middle of the process.

441
00:30:44,000 --> 00:30:45,000
 Listen to this.

442
00:30:45,000 --> 00:30:47,000
 My wife has this thing called caterpillar soup.

443
00:30:47,000 --> 00:30:50,000
 She's a counselor. This is a counseling term, apparently, or at least hers.

444
00:30:50,000 --> 00:30:52,000
 Let me explain.

445
00:30:52,000 --> 00:30:56,000
 When a caterpillar is in the process of the chrysalis to turn into a butterfly,

446
00:30:56,000 --> 00:30:59,000
 the caterpillar gets to the middle space,

447
00:30:59,000 --> 00:31:02,000
 where it's no longer recognizable as a caterpillar,

448
00:31:02,000 --> 00:31:05,000
 but it is not yet a beautiful butterfly.

449
00:31:05,000 --> 00:31:07,000
 This is the middle of the change.

450
00:31:07,000 --> 00:31:11,000
 And at this point, scientists call it caterpillar soup.

451
00:31:11,000 --> 00:31:15,000
 The old is gone, but the new has not yet come.

452
00:31:15,000 --> 00:31:20,000
 And when we're in that place, the caterpillar is the most vulnerable.

453
00:31:20,000 --> 00:31:23,000
 And when we're in a place in the middle of a transformation process,

454
00:31:23,000 --> 00:31:26,000
 we might get to a situation where our old self,

455
00:31:26,000 --> 00:31:28,000
 we've actually begun to deal with some stuff.

456
00:31:28,000 --> 00:31:30,000
 God's convicted us. We brought our sin to Him.

457
00:31:30,000 --> 00:31:33,000
 We feel like we're being liberated from some of that old stuff,

458
00:31:33,000 --> 00:31:36,000
 but we recognize that our new stuff is not yet here,

459
00:31:36,000 --> 00:31:38,000
 and we're in this middle,

460
00:31:38,000 --> 00:31:42,000
 and it's there that the enemy will attack us and make us feel overwhelmed.

461
00:31:42,000 --> 00:31:44,000
 Notice how it says it here.

462
00:31:44,000 --> 00:31:47,000
 They actually say this, that people have lost their strength,

463
00:31:47,000 --> 00:31:51,000
 and there's so much rubble that we cannot rebuild the wall.

464
00:31:51,000 --> 00:31:53,000
 Notice this. I think this is funny.

465
00:31:53,000 --> 00:31:57,000
 They say, "There's so much rubble. How could we ever do this?"

466
00:31:57,000 --> 00:32:00,000
 And you could just stand back from a logical perspective and say,

467
00:32:00,000 --> 00:32:05,000
 "Hang on a sec. There's 50% less rubble than when you started,

468
00:32:05,000 --> 00:32:07,000
 because when you started, it was all rubble,

469
00:32:07,000 --> 00:32:10,000
 but you've now rebuilt half of the wall.

470
00:32:10,000 --> 00:32:14,000
 So literally, logically, there's 50% less."

471
00:32:14,000 --> 00:32:17,000
 But when we're in that caterpillar soup moment,

472
00:32:17,000 --> 00:32:20,000
 and we've let go, but we haven't yet fully been changed,

473
00:32:20,000 --> 00:32:23,000
 we find ourselves in that vulnerable place

474
00:32:23,000 --> 00:32:25,000
 where everything feels like it's coming in upon us,

475
00:32:25,000 --> 00:32:28,000
 and we'll begin to look at what is still around us,

476
00:32:28,000 --> 00:32:32,000
 and we're like, "There's so much still to be done.

477
00:32:32,000 --> 00:32:36,000
 I can't do it. I mean, I'm exhausted already,

478
00:32:36,000 --> 00:32:38,000
 and I'm only halfway through.

479
00:32:38,000 --> 00:32:40,000
 Do you really think I can do this?

480
00:32:40,000 --> 00:32:44,000
 There's so much rubble still here."

481
00:32:44,000 --> 00:32:49,000
 That's the enemy's strategy, to cause you in that middle moment

482
00:32:49,000 --> 00:32:53,000
 to see all the things that are to come and say,

483
00:32:53,000 --> 00:32:57,000
 "You'll never get there. It's not going to happen for you.

484
00:32:57,000 --> 00:33:02,000
 You may as well put the tools down now."

485
00:33:02,000 --> 00:33:04,000
 The third opposition that will come to you

486
00:33:04,000 --> 00:33:07,000
 in any season of personal transformation,

487
00:33:07,000 --> 00:33:10,000
 usually at the end of that season,

488
00:33:10,000 --> 00:33:13,000
 is the opposition of compromise.

489
00:33:13,000 --> 00:33:16,000
 Let me read this to you from Nehemiah 6, starting in verse 1.

490
00:33:16,000 --> 00:33:21,000
 "When the word came to Sambalat, Tobiah, Geshem, and the Arabs,

491
00:33:21,000 --> 00:33:24,000
 and the rest of our enemies, that I had rebuilt the wall,

492
00:33:24,000 --> 00:33:27,000
 and not a gap was left in it, though up to that time

493
00:33:27,000 --> 00:33:30,000
 I had not yet set the doors in the gates."

494
00:33:30,000 --> 00:33:31,000
 Now notice this.

495
00:33:31,000 --> 00:33:34,000
 So they have now almost completed the project.

496
00:33:34,000 --> 00:33:36,000
 All the walls have been constructed, but the gates,

497
00:33:36,000 --> 00:33:39,000
 and there were many gates around the old walls of Jerusalem,

498
00:33:39,000 --> 00:33:41,000
 were not yet set in place.

499
00:33:41,000 --> 00:33:44,000
 So the project's not done yet, but it's right towards the end.

500
00:33:44,000 --> 00:33:46,000
 It's like he's been running a marathon,

501
00:33:46,000 --> 00:33:49,000
 he's entered into the stadium, but he's still got two laps.

502
00:33:49,000 --> 00:33:51,000
 Are you with me?

503
00:33:51,000 --> 00:33:53,000
 And then he says this.

504
00:33:53,000 --> 00:33:56,000
 He says, "Sambalat and Geshem sent me this message.

505
00:33:56,000 --> 00:34:03,000
 'Come, let us meet together in one of the villages on the plain of Ono.'"

506
00:34:03,000 --> 00:34:05,000
 Notice this.

507
00:34:05,000 --> 00:34:07,000
 Right at the end of the project,

508
00:34:07,000 --> 00:34:10,000
 the enemies come with their final opposition.

509
00:34:10,000 --> 00:34:12,000
 And here's the opposition.

510
00:34:12,000 --> 00:34:14,000
 "Hey, just come.

511
00:34:14,000 --> 00:34:18,000
 Come with us to the villages on the plains of Ono."

512
00:34:18,000 --> 00:34:21,000
 The modern equivalent of this would be like right towards the end

513
00:34:21,000 --> 00:34:24,000
 of an important project where you need to be there leading that project,

514
00:34:24,000 --> 00:34:27,000
 whether that's a transformation you or something at work,

515
00:34:27,000 --> 00:34:29,000
 and then somebody comes to you and says,

516
00:34:29,000 --> 00:34:33,000
 "Hey, why don't we just escape for a little while to the beaches of Bali?

517
00:34:33,000 --> 00:34:35,000
 (Laughter)

518
00:34:35,000 --> 00:34:37,000
 Why don't we just get away?

519
00:34:37,000 --> 00:34:39,000
 Oh, you've worked so hard.

520
00:34:39,000 --> 00:34:41,000
 You tried your best.

521
00:34:41,000 --> 00:34:44,000
 Look, you've actually accomplished so much.

522
00:34:44,000 --> 00:34:47,000
 Why don't you just put the tools down?

523
00:34:47,000 --> 00:34:48,000
 You deserve it.

524
00:34:48,000 --> 00:34:50,000
 You've worked hard.

525
00:34:50,000 --> 00:34:52,000
 Why don't you just look after yourself a little bit?

526
00:34:52,000 --> 00:34:55,000
 Man, you've been giving to everyone.

527
00:34:55,000 --> 00:34:57,000
 Now is the time to give to yourself.

528
00:34:57,000 --> 00:35:01,000
 Let's just retreat to the plains of Ono."

529
00:35:01,000 --> 00:35:06,000
 The plains of Ono were about a whole day's journey north from Jerusalem.

530
00:35:06,000 --> 00:35:08,000
 In fact, it would--this is Sambalat speaking--

531
00:35:08,000 --> 00:35:13,000
 have placed, if Nehemiah had gone, placed him very close to Samaria itself

532
00:35:13,000 --> 00:35:15,000
 and to the power of the armies there.

533
00:35:15,000 --> 00:35:18,000
 Nehemiah actually discerns that that was their strategy.

534
00:35:18,000 --> 00:35:20,000
 But Ono is this fascinating place.

535
00:35:20,000 --> 00:35:22,000
 It was a beautiful plain.

536
00:35:22,000 --> 00:35:23,000
 Many villages were there.

537
00:35:23,000 --> 00:35:27,000
 And these were relatively wealthy villages in those days.

538
00:35:27,000 --> 00:35:30,000
 It was actually a craftsman's village.

539
00:35:30,000 --> 00:35:32,000
 So it's very likely that some of the builders of the wall,

540
00:35:32,000 --> 00:35:34,000
 some of the craftsmen at the temple,

541
00:35:34,000 --> 00:35:38,000
 were from these villages in the plain of Ono.

542
00:35:38,000 --> 00:35:40,000
 What Sambalat's trying to do is to say,

543
00:35:40,000 --> 00:35:43,000
 "Hey, look, you deserve to look after yourself a little bit.

544
00:35:43,000 --> 00:35:45,000
 You deserve to give to yourself.

545
00:35:45,000 --> 00:35:48,000
 Man, you've been working on behalf of everybody else.

546
00:35:48,000 --> 00:35:50,000
 You've been working on behalf of your God.

547
00:35:50,000 --> 00:35:52,000
 Just put your tools down right before the end.

548
00:35:52,000 --> 00:35:53,000
 Why don't you just come?"

549
00:35:53,000 --> 00:35:55,000
 And it'll be like somebody standing in that stadium

550
00:35:55,000 --> 00:35:57,000
 and shouting to the marathon runner,

551
00:35:57,000 --> 00:36:00,000
 "You've done great. You've run so far.

552
00:36:00,000 --> 00:36:02,000
 Look, just come and sit here for a moment."

553
00:36:02,000 --> 00:36:05,000
 Like two more laps around and you're done.

554
00:36:05,000 --> 00:36:07,000
 But no, no, no, just come sit down for a minute.

555
00:36:07,000 --> 00:36:08,000
 Why don't you just rest?

556
00:36:08,000 --> 00:36:09,000
 Let everybody else run by you.

557
00:36:09,000 --> 00:36:11,000
 Let's just rest for a bit.

558
00:36:11,000 --> 00:36:13,000
 You've earned your rest.

559
00:36:13,000 --> 00:36:16,000
 Well done, my good and faithful servant.

560
00:36:16,000 --> 00:36:19,000
 The power of compromise right towards the end of it.

561
00:36:19,000 --> 00:36:21,000
 Here's what it's designed to do.

562
00:36:21,000 --> 00:36:23,000
 It's designed to make you settle

563
00:36:23,000 --> 00:36:27,000
 for three quarters of your transformation.

564
00:36:27,000 --> 00:36:29,000
 See, God starts you out on a process of transformation,

565
00:36:29,000 --> 00:36:31,000
 and he has a picture in mind of who he's desiring

566
00:36:31,000 --> 00:36:32,000
 for you to be.

567
00:36:32,000 --> 00:36:34,000
 And sometimes he gives us the idea of what that is,

568
00:36:34,000 --> 00:36:37,000
 and we're like, "Wow, could I ever be like that?

569
00:36:37,000 --> 00:36:40,000
 Could that rubble ever be restored like that?"

570
00:36:40,000 --> 00:36:43,000
 And here's the temptation and the opposition of compromise.

571
00:36:43,000 --> 00:36:44,000
 As we enter into that stadium,

572
00:36:44,000 --> 00:36:47,000
 we want to take that seat and not complete the two laps,

573
00:36:47,000 --> 00:36:48,000
 because here's what we're thinking.

574
00:36:48,000 --> 00:36:52,000
 "I'm okay with three quarters.

575
00:36:52,000 --> 00:36:53,000
 I mean, have you seen who I am?

576
00:36:53,000 --> 00:36:56,000
 I'm not the person I used to be a few months ago.

577
00:36:56,000 --> 00:36:58,000
 I mean, God's already done so much in me.

578
00:36:58,000 --> 00:37:00,000
 God's already transformed so much.

579
00:37:00,000 --> 00:37:01,000
 It was hard work.

580
00:37:01,000 --> 00:37:02,000
 I had to pray about it.

581
00:37:02,000 --> 00:37:04,000
 I had to fight all that opposition.

582
00:37:04,000 --> 00:37:05,000
 I went into therapy.

583
00:37:05,000 --> 00:37:06,000
 It was difficult.

584
00:37:06,000 --> 00:37:08,000
 Look, I know I'm only three quarters changed,

585
00:37:08,000 --> 00:37:11,000
 but a three-quarter changed me is better than the me

586
00:37:11,000 --> 00:37:13,000
 two months ago."

587
00:37:13,000 --> 00:37:17,000
 And so the temptation that we have is to say

588
00:37:17,000 --> 00:37:22,000
 three quarters of what God wants is enough.

589
00:37:22,000 --> 00:37:27,000
 The enemy loves for you to settle just short

590
00:37:27,000 --> 00:37:31,000
 of full redemption, full restoration, full healing,

591
00:37:31,000 --> 00:37:34,000
 full life, because he knows if he can get you to stop

592
00:37:34,000 --> 00:37:37,000
 at three quarters, then after a while,

593
00:37:37,000 --> 00:37:39,000
 that's going to become 50%.

594
00:37:39,000 --> 00:37:41,000
 And after a while, that's going to become a quarter.

595
00:37:41,000 --> 00:37:47,000
 And then just a few years later, you're back to where you began.

596
00:37:47,000 --> 00:37:52,000
 That compromise is so a wrestle for us.

597
00:37:52,000 --> 00:37:53,000
 Here's an interesting thing.

598
00:37:53,000 --> 00:37:57,000
 The word "ono" actually means grief,

599
00:37:57,000 --> 00:38:02,000
 which is really quite fascinating because any time

600
00:38:02,000 --> 00:38:05,000
 you leave a place where God wants you to be,

601
00:38:05,000 --> 00:38:07,000
 to go where Satan wants you to go,

602
00:38:07,000 --> 00:38:10,000
 you'll always end up in a place of grief.

603
00:38:10,000 --> 00:38:12,000
 Whenever you make that decision,

604
00:38:12,000 --> 00:38:15,000
 "I'm going to deviate from the place that I know

605
00:38:15,000 --> 00:38:19,000
 God has asked me to be in and God is calling me to be in

606
00:38:19,000 --> 00:38:21,000
 and the work that God is calling into my hands to do,

607
00:38:21,000 --> 00:38:23,000
 and I'm going to deviate from that,"

608
00:38:23,000 --> 00:38:28,000
 you're going to end up in a place of grief.

609
00:38:28,000 --> 00:38:32,000
 So these three oppositions, the opposition of ridicule

610
00:38:32,000 --> 00:38:35,000
 right at the start, the opposition of being overwhelmed

611
00:38:35,000 --> 00:38:37,000
 in the middle, and the opposition of compromise

612
00:38:37,000 --> 00:38:39,000
 at the end, come together to try to hold us back.

613
00:38:39,000 --> 00:38:42,000
 And the question is, what can we do?

614
00:38:42,000 --> 00:38:44,000
 Knowing that the Lord is not going to remove

615
00:38:44,000 --> 00:38:47,000
 these oppositions for us, what can we do when they come?

616
00:38:47,000 --> 00:38:50,000
 What is the strategy that is on God's heart

617
00:38:50,000 --> 00:38:53,000
 to help us to stand up and steadfast

618
00:38:53,000 --> 00:38:55,000
 when these oppositions are with us?

619
00:38:55,000 --> 00:38:57,000
 Well, let me close by taking you to this bit

620
00:38:57,000 --> 00:39:02,000
 that Nehemiah does right here in chapter 6, verse 9.

621
00:39:02,000 --> 00:39:05,000
 Nehemiah says, "They were all trying to frighten us,

622
00:39:05,000 --> 00:39:09,000
 thinking their hands will get too weak for the work

623
00:39:09,000 --> 00:39:11,000
 and it will not be completed.

624
00:39:11,000 --> 00:39:13,000
 But here's what I prayed.

625
00:39:13,000 --> 00:39:17,000
 Now strengthen my hands."

626
00:39:17,000 --> 00:39:19,000
 There's this beautiful moment here because

627
00:39:19,000 --> 00:39:21,000
 I love the honesty of Nehemiah.

628
00:39:21,000 --> 00:39:23,000
 He's like, "Man, we went through these oppositions

629
00:39:23,000 --> 00:39:25,000
 and these oppositions were tough," he says.

630
00:39:25,000 --> 00:39:27,000
 "And each time that these oppositions came,

631
00:39:27,000 --> 00:39:30,000
 we were weakened as a people."

632
00:39:30,000 --> 00:39:33,000
 And the strategy of these oppositions, Nehemiah is saying,

633
00:39:33,000 --> 00:39:35,000
 is that they were all designed to put fear in us

634
00:39:35,000 --> 00:39:38,000
 so that we would think, mentally begin to think,

635
00:39:38,000 --> 00:39:42,000
 that we cannot in our own strength

636
00:39:42,000 --> 00:39:45,000
 achieve what God has asked us to do.

637
00:39:45,000 --> 00:39:47,000
 And it's almost like Nehemiah is saying,

638
00:39:47,000 --> 00:39:49,000
 "You need to understand that you cannot achieve

639
00:39:49,000 --> 00:39:53,000
 in your own strength what the Lord has called you to do."

640
00:39:53,000 --> 00:39:56,000
 Like, let's just get that clear right here,

641
00:39:56,000 --> 00:39:57,000
 Nehemiah is saying to his people.

642
00:39:57,000 --> 00:39:59,000
 You can't. You will never have enough wisdom,

643
00:39:59,000 --> 00:40:02,000
 never have enough knowledge, never have enough strength,

644
00:40:02,000 --> 00:40:05,000
 never have enough whatever, never have enough resources

645
00:40:05,000 --> 00:40:09,000
 to do yourself what God has asked you to do.

646
00:40:09,000 --> 00:40:11,000
 That's not the way God works.

647
00:40:11,000 --> 00:40:13,000
 He doesn't expect you to find all of that resource

648
00:40:13,000 --> 00:40:14,000
 and strength in yourself.

649
00:40:14,000 --> 00:40:17,000
 In fact, the starting point is to say,

650
00:40:17,000 --> 00:40:20,000
 "I am a sinner in need of a Savior.

651
00:40:20,000 --> 00:40:24,000
 I am weak, but He is strong.

652
00:40:24,000 --> 00:40:29,000
 I am afraid, but perfect love can cast out my fear."

653
00:40:29,000 --> 00:40:31,000
 It is to start in that place of saying,

654
00:40:31,000 --> 00:40:33,000
 "This is who I am. I know who I am.

655
00:40:33,000 --> 00:40:35,000
 And as soon as I begin to arrogantly think

656
00:40:35,000 --> 00:40:39,000
 that I can do this in my own strength, I will fail."

657
00:40:39,000 --> 00:40:40,000
 But here's the thing.

658
00:40:40,000 --> 00:40:42,000
 Nehemiah stands before his people and he says,

659
00:40:42,000 --> 00:40:44,000
 "Honestly, I'm with you.

660
00:40:44,000 --> 00:40:47,000
 I felt scared. I felt weak throughout this whole process.

661
00:40:47,000 --> 00:40:50,000
 But guess what? It's not about our own strength.

662
00:40:50,000 --> 00:40:54,000
 It's about His equipment, His resource, His knowledge,

663
00:40:54,000 --> 00:40:58,000
 His beauty, His power, His grace, His strength."

664
00:40:58,000 --> 00:41:00,000
 So here's what I'm going to pray.

665
00:41:00,000 --> 00:41:06,000
 I'm going to pray that His strength would come, not my own.

666
00:41:06,000 --> 00:41:09,000
 His wisdom, not my wisdom.

667
00:41:09,000 --> 00:41:12,000
 His thoughts, higher than my thoughts.

668
00:41:12,000 --> 00:41:15,000
 But notice also what Nehemiah prays.

669
00:41:15,000 --> 00:41:18,000
 He first of all establishes the reality that he's weak

670
00:41:18,000 --> 00:41:20,000
 and God's strong and he wants God's strength.

671
00:41:20,000 --> 00:41:24,000
 But notice this. He says, "But in my hands, Lord."

672
00:41:24,000 --> 00:41:25,000
 In other words, he does not pray,

673
00:41:25,000 --> 00:41:31,000
 "God, strengthen the angels to wipe out the enemies."

674
00:41:31,000 --> 00:41:35,000
 He understands that the greatest way to push back Satan

675
00:41:35,000 --> 00:41:38,000
 is to be strengthened for the work that God has called him to do.

676
00:41:38,000 --> 00:41:42,000
 The number one thing in spiritual warfare, and yes, we need to pray.

677
00:41:42,000 --> 00:41:44,000
 Yes, we need to do all the things that we do in spiritual warfare.

678
00:41:44,000 --> 00:41:47,000
 The number one thing in spiritual warfare that pushes the enemy back

679
00:41:47,000 --> 00:41:50,000
 is the steadfastness of the body of Christ

680
00:41:50,000 --> 00:41:55,000
 to not let go of the work that Christ has called them to.

681
00:41:55,000 --> 00:41:59,000
 That pushes the gates of hell back more than anything else.

682
00:41:59,000 --> 00:42:02,000
 And so Nehemiah says, "My hands."

683
00:42:02,000 --> 00:42:04,000
 The very things that you've asked to do,

684
00:42:04,000 --> 00:42:08,000
 the moving of the stones bit by bit, the establishing of the doors.

685
00:42:08,000 --> 00:42:09,000
 I've got to do that work.

686
00:42:09,000 --> 00:42:11,000
 You're not going to miraculously do that work for me.

687
00:42:11,000 --> 00:42:15,000
 But what you can do miraculously is put your strength inside of me

688
00:42:15,000 --> 00:42:18,000
 that will change how I think, change how I know,

689
00:42:18,000 --> 00:42:22,000
 change what I believe about myself, and I will take with my hands,

